summaries.short: Hannah gets an idea as to what her life might be like if she'd stuck around her hometown in Michigan.
summaries.full: Hannah's parents fly her back to Michigan to celebrate their 30th wedding anniversary. Though they hope she'll go on their date, she gets one of her own instead, and catches up with some high-school friends who are mourning a hometown tragedy.

titles.full: Welcome to Bushwick a.k.a. The Crackcident

summaries.short: The girls face surprising revelations and a few inquiries at a wild party in Bushwick.
summaries.full: At the 'best party ever' in Bushwick, Brooklyn, Hannah learns Adam's main defining trait (other than his ears), Marnie is beside herself (and annoying others) after seeing Charlie, Jessa teases a mystery texter, and Ray becomes Shoshanna's spirit guide in a time of need.

summaries.short: Hannah is confused by her boss's mixed signals, as well as Adam's.
summaries.full: At Jessa's advice, Hannah decides to better her story by propositioning her boss. She subsequently retreats to Adam, who has a different idea about the state of their union. Meanwhile, Marnie and Charlie assess their relationship, and Jessa is determined to reconquer an ex.

summaries.full: Hannah ventures further into Adam's world, for better and for worse. Newly unemployed Jessa, and Marnie, at an all-time low, bond unexpectedly and meet a very eligible bachelor (Chris O'Dowd) who is not what he seems.

summaries.short: Hannah takes up 'sexting'; Shoshanna runs into a boy from summer camp; Jessa gets distracted on the job; Ray and Charlie snoop.
summaries.full: Adam sends Hannah a 'sext' message that puts her in a tailspin. Meanwhile, Hannah's boss gets touchy at her office job, Shoshanna reunites with a boy from sleepaway camp, Jessa gets distracted while watching her charges, and Ray and Charlie snoop through the girls' apartment.

summaries.short: Hannah decides to take some chances after colliding with Marnie over rent money and seeing a former classmate get published.
summaries.full: Behind on rent and resentful of the literary success of a former classmate (Jenny Slate), Hannah starts work at Grumpy Cafe and does a reading hosted by a former professor (Michael Imperioli). Marnie finds it increasingly difficult to support Hannah financially and emotionally. Jessa is confronted by her former boss, and Shoshanna goes on a day date with an online match.
